Võ Thị Lan Chi is an Intern Network Engineer with 0 years of commercial experience. Their core expertise lies in Network Configuration, Network Monitoring, and Troubleshooting using VPN architectures, with a strong foundation in Network Administration and Network Design concepts. They have worked on various academic projects, including Deploying, Managing, and Configuring VPN, Designing a Network System for a Small Business, and Building a System for Booking Classrooms/Meeting Rooms with IoT Integration and User Authentication, demonstrating their ability to apply theoretical knowledge to practical problems. These projects have equipped them with a deep understanding of network systems and the ability to design and implement secure and efficient networks.

Technically, they are proficient in programming languages such as HTML, CSS, Python, Java, and SQL, and have hands-on experience with tools and platforms like Virtual Box, VMware, Terminal, PowerShell, Command Prompt, LaTeX, Word, Excel, PowerPoint, and Canva. They also have a solid understanding of database management systems, particularly SQL, and are familiar with IoT and virtualization concepts. Their academic background in Computer Networks and Data Communication at Ton Duc Thang University has provided them with a strong foundation in network fundamentals, protocols, and architectures. With a strong focus on network engineering and a keen interest in emerging technologies like IoT and virtualization, Võ Thị Lan Chi is well-equipped to contribute to network design, implementation, and administration projects, and is poised to grow into a skilled network engineer with further experience and training.